@node 3_19__31_01_2026_ "3.19 (31.01.2026)"
@{i}3.19 (31.01.2026)@{ui}

  * @{b}Fork of 3.18@{ub}
    * Set English as default localization for fat95 handler
    * Rebuild by vasm 2.0d
    * Consolidated documentation into fat95.guide

  * Detect SFS/PFS/FFS/RDB as foreign disk formats

  * @{b}GPT partition table support@{ub}
    * Automatic detection of GPT disks via protective MBR (type 0xEE)
    * Scans GPT partition entries for Microsoft Basic Data partitions (FAT)
    * Supports partition selection via DosType (same as MBR: FAT\1, FAT\2, etc.)

  * @{b}Improved disk change handling@{ub}
    * Non-existent partitions now show "No Disk" instead of "Uninitialized"
    * Fixes stale partition data when switching to cards with fewer partitions
      (see @{"Disk Status Meanings" link disk_status_meanings} )
    * Foreign disk formats (RDB, PFS, SFS) show appropriate status per partition

  * @{b}Bug fixes@{ub}
    * Fixed trailing slashes in path names (e.g., "makedir cf0:temp/" now
      correctly creates "temp")
    WARNING: Using trailing slashes with 3.18 corrupted the filesystem

----------------------------------------
@{"<< Prev" link What_s_New_in}  @{"Contents" link Main}  @{"Next >>" link Installation}

@endnode

@node Installation "Installation"
@{b}Installation@{ub}

@{b}Introduction@{ub}

Installing disk drives under AmigaOS requires @{i}two@{ui} components:

  1. A @{b}hardware driver@{ub} that provides block-level access to the drive. This can be
     part of the Kickstart ROM (e.g., @{fg shine}trackdisk.device@{fg text} ) or a separate file (e.g.,
     @{fg shine}Devs:compactflash.device@{fg text} ).
  2. A @{b}filesystem handler@{ub} that manages partitions, directories, and files. The
     standard filesystem is in ROM. Others, like fat95, are files in the @{fg shine}L:@{fg text}
     drawer.

These two components are connected via a @{b}mountlist@{ub} - a configuration
file that tells AmigaOS how to mount the drive.

@{b}Installation@{ub}

  1. Edit the @{fg shine}install_fat95@{fg text} text file for your language.
  2. Double-click the @{fg shine}install_fat95@{fg text} icon to activate the changes.
  3. Optionally double-click example mountlist icons in @{fg shine}DOSDrivers/@{fg text}:
    * @{fg shine}MS0@{fg text}/@{fg shine}MS1@{fg text} - FAT-formatted PC DD 720k floppy (mfm.device)
    * @{fg shine}CF0@{fg text} - FAT partition on CompactFlash in PCMCIA slot (compactflash.device),
      supports MBR and GPT
   For custom configurations, see the @{"Mountlist Configuration" link mountlist_configuration} section.
  4. Copy mountlists to:
    * @{fg shine}DEVS:DOSDrivers/@{fg text} for automatic mounting at boot, or
    * @{fg shine}SYS:Storage/DOSDrives/@{fg text} for manual mounting via shell command (Method A:
      Shell Command)

----------------------------------------
@{"<< Prev" link 3_19__31_01_2026_}  @{"Contents" link Main}  @{"Next >>" link Mountlist_Configuration}

@endnode

